<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Combined Respiratory Vaccine Survey - Form</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <style>
    /* 圆形checkbox样式 */
    input[type="checkbox"] {
      appearance: none;
      -webkit-appearance: none;
      -moz-appearance: none;
      width: 18px;
      height: 18px;
      border: 2px solid #999;
      border-radius: 50%;
      outline: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      position: relative;
      vertical-align: middle;
      margin-right: 8px;
    }
    
    input[type="checkbox"]:checked {
      background-color: #007bff;
      border-color: #007bff;
    }
    
    input[type="checkbox"]:checked::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: 50%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
      width: 8px;
      height: 8px;
      background-color: white;
      border-radius: 50%;
    }
    
    input[type="checkbox"]:hover {
      border-color: #007bff;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Acceptability of a Combined Respiratory Influenza-COVID-19 Vaccine Among Nursing Students in Hong Kong</h1>
    <form action="/survey" method="POST">
      <!-- Section 1: Demographics -->
      <h2>Section 1: Demographics</h2>
      <p>Please provide the following information about yourself.</p>
      <div class="section">
        <label>What is your age?</label><br>
        <input type="text" name="age" placeholder="e.g., 18-20, 21-23" required>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>What is your sex?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="sex" value="Male" required> Male
        <input type="radio" name="sex" value="Female"> Female
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>Which nursing education program are you currently enrolled in?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="program" value="HighDiploma" required> High Diploma in Nursing<br>
        <input type="radio" name="program" value="Bachelor"> Bachelor of Nursing<br>
        <input type="radio" name="program" value="Postgraduate"> Postgraduate programmes (Nursing)<br>
        <input type="radio" name="program" value="Doctorate"> Doctorate (DCS, PhD)
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: Vaccination History -->
      <h2>Section 2: Vaccination History</h2>
      <p>Please indicate your vaccination status.</p>
      <div class="section">
        <label>Have you received the seasonal influenza vaccine in the past 12 months?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="fluVaccine12m" value="Yes" required> Yes
        <input type="radio" name="fluVaccine12m" value="No"> No
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>Have you received any Covid-19 vaccine dose (primary series or booster) in the past 12 months?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="covidVaccine12m" value="Yes" required> Yes
        <input type="radio" name="covidVaccine12m" value="No"> No
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>Have you ever experienced side effects from any respiratory virus vaccine (e.g., flu, Covid-19)?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="sideEffects" value="VerySerious" required> Yes, very serious side effects (difficulty breathing, serious allergic reaction, high fever)<br>
        <input type="radio" name="sideEffects" value="Moderate"> Yes, moderate side effects (persistent cough, moderate fever, swelling)<br>
        <input type="radio" name="sideEffects" value="VeryMild"> Yes, very mild side effects (soreness or redness, mild fatigue, slight headache)<br>
        <input type="radio" name="sideEffects" value="No"> No
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>Have you heard about live attenuated or inactivated (traditional) vaccines?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="heardTraditional" value="Yes" required> Yes
        <input type="radio" name="heardTraditional" value="No"> No
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>Have you heard about mRNA vaccines?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="heardMRNA" value="Yes" required> Yes
        <input type="radio" name="heardMRNA" value="No"> No
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3: Knowledge Assessment -->
      <h2>Section 3: Knowledge Assessment</h2>
      <p>Please answer the following 7 questions to the best of your knowledge. They include true/false and multiple-choice formats. There are no right or wrong answers—this is simply to help us gauge your baseline knowledge.</p>
      <div class="section">
        <label>1. Approximately what percentage of the global population is infected with influenza annually?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="q1" value="a" required> a) Less than 5%<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> b) 5-10%<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> c) 20-30%<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q1" value="d"> d) More than 50%
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>2. True or False: Influenza is primarily transmitted through airborne droplets from coughing or sneezing.</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="q2" value="True" required> a) True
        <input type="radio" name="q2" value="False"> b) False
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>3. How often should influenza vaccines be administered?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="q3" value="a" required> a) Every year<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q3" value="b"> b) Every five years<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q3" value="c"> c) Once in a lifetime<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q3" value="d"> d) I don't know
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>4. True or False: Covid-19 vaccines have been shown to reduce severe outcomes (hospitalization/death) by over 80% in most studies.</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="q4" value="True" required> a) True
        <input type="radio" name="q4" value="False"> b) False
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>5. Which of the following is a common mode of Covid-19 transmission?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="q5" value="a" required> a) Only through contaminated surfaces<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q5" value="b"> b) Airborne via respiratory droplets and aerosols<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q5" value="c"> c) Exclusively through food/water<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q5" value="d"> d) Insect bites
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>6. Which of the following vaccines uses mRNA technologies?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="q6" value="a" required> a) Influenza vaccine<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q6" value="b"> b) Covid-19 vaccine Comirnaty (Pfizer/ BioNTech)<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q6" value="c"> c) Covid-19 vaccine Sinovac<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q6" value="d"> d) Infant BCG vaccine<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q6" value="e"> e) Measles, Mumps, Rubella & Varicella Infant (MMRV) vaccine
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>7. What is the purpose of influenza or Covid-19 vaccines?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="q7" value="a" required> a) To treat diseases<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q7" value="b"> b) To prevent infection<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q7" value="c"> c) To lower the severity of complications even if infected<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q7" value="d"> d) Both options b and c
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4: Attitudes Toward a Combined Vaccine -->
      <h2>Section 4: Attitudes Toward a Combined Vaccine (Health Belief Model)</h2>
      <p>The following 12 questions ask about your perceptions of a hypothetical new combined vaccine that protects against influenza and Covid-19 in a single shot.</p>
      <p>For each statement, please rate your agreement on a scale of 1-5.</p>
      <p><strong>1 = Strongly Disagree | 2 = Disagree | 3 = Neutral | 4 = Agree | 5 = Strongly Agree</strong></p>
      <div class="section">
        <p>1. I am particularly concerned about severe complications from influenza or Covid-19 viruses (e.g., hospitalization, long-term side effects).</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude1" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude1" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude1" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude1" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude1" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>2. A combined vaccine would effectively reduce my risk of getting sick from influenza and Covid-19 viruses.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude2" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude2" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude2" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude2" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude2" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>3. Getting a combined vaccine would make it easier for me to stay protected without multiple shots, benefiting my busy schedule as a student.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude3" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude3" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude3" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude3" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude3" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>4. I worry about the potential side effects and safety of a new combined vaccine.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude4" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude4" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude4" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude4" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude4" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>5. I worry that a combined vaccine will have reduced efficacy and offer less protection.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude5" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude5" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude5" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude5" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude5" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>6. The cost or access to this vaccine might prevent me from getting it.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude6" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude6" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude6" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude6" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude6" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>7. A recommendation from my nursing instructor or healthcare provider would strongly encourage me to receive the combined vaccine.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude7" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude7" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude7" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude7" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude7" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>8. Public health campaigns or University Campus offering free combined vaccines would prompt me to act.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude8" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude8" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude8" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude8" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude8" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>9. I am more willing to receive an mRNA-based influenza vaccine than a traditional one (an inactivated or live attenuated vaccine).</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude9" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude9" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude9" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude9" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude9" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>10. I have a basic understanding of how mRNA vaccines work when compared to traditional vaccines (live attenuated and inactivated vaccines).</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude10" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude10" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude10" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude10" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude10" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>11. I believe that the vaccines produced using mRNA technology are safe.</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude11" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude11" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude11" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude11" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude11" value="5"> Strongly agree

        <p>12. I believe that the vaccines produced using mRNA technology are more effective than the traditional vaccines (live attenuated or inactivated vaccines).</p>
        <input type="radio" name="attitude12" value="1" required> Strongly disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude12" value="2"> Disagree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude12" value="3"> Neutral
        <input type="radio" name="attitude12" value="4"> Agree
        <input type="radio" name="attitude12" value="5"> Strongly agree
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5: Intention to Vaccinate -->
      <h2>Section 5: Intention to Vaccinate</h2>
      <div class="section">
        <label>If a combined annual respiratory vaccine against both influenza and Covid-19 were available, how likely would you be to receive it?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="intentionCombined" value="VeryUnlikely" required> Very unlikely
        <input type="radio" name="intentionCombined" value="Unlikely"> Unlikely
        <input type="radio" name="intentionCombined" value="Likely"> Likely
        <input type="radio" name="intentionCombined" value="VeryLikely"> Very likely
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>How likely would you be to receive this combined vaccine if it utilized mRNA technology (like the Covid-19 Pfizer/ BioNTech vaccine)?</label><br>
        <input type="radio" name="intentionMRNA" value="VeryUnlikely" required> Very unlikely
        <input type="radio" name="intentionMRNA" value="Unlikely"> Unlikely
        <input type="radio" name="intentionMRNA" value="Likely"> Likely
        <input type="radio" name="intentionMRNA" value="VeryLikely"> Very likely
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>What factors would influence your decision to receive the combined vaccine? (Select all that apply)</label><br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="factors" value="HealthcareProfessionals"> Recommendations from healthcare professionals<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="factors" value="Peers"> Information from peers<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="factors" value="PersonalBeliefs"> Personal health beliefs<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="factors" value="mRNATechnology"> It is a vaccine using the new mRNA technology<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="factors" value="SingleShot"> Do not have to take multiple vaccine shots because one vaccine can protect against multiple diseases<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="factors" value="Others"> Others
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <label>What are the main barriers you see to getting a combined respiratory virus vaccine? (Select all that apply)</label><br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="barriers" value="Safety"> Safety concerns<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="barriers" value="Efficacy"> Efficacy<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="barriers" value="Costs"> Costs<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="barriers" value="mRNA"> mRNA technologies<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="barriers" value="PersonalBeliefs"> Personal beliefs<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="barriers" value="Others"> Others
      </div>

      <button type="submit" class="btn">Submit Survey</button>
    </form>
    <p><strong>Thank you for completing the survey! Your input is greatly appreciated.</strong></p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
